ent":"datamark does not bundle a validator. Instead, it implements the **Standard Schema v1** interface, a cross-library specification that Zod, Valibot, ArkType, TypeBox, and others support."},"250":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-5","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#standard-schema-v1","content":"Any object with a `~standard` property implementing the spec can be passed as a schema:"},"251":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-6","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#validation-in-the-parse-pipeline","content":"When a schema is provided, `parse()` validates the generator's return value automatically. If validation fails, it throws `ValidationError` with structured issue data:"},"252":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-7","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#validation-in-the-parse-pipeline","content":"Asynchronous schema validation is not supported. Use synchronous validators like Zod or Valibot."},"253":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-8","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#supported-validators","content":"Library"},"254":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-9","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#supported-validators","content":"Status"},"255":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-10","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#supported-validators","content":"Zod"},"256":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-11","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explanation/validation#supported-validators","content":"✅ Supported"},"257":{"id":"/docs/explanation/validation-12","page_id":"/docs/explanation/validation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/explana